<p>Social media for a cleaning company is the fastest way to fill your schedule without spending thousands on ads. Cleaning businesses that post regularly see <a href="https://www.zenmaid.com/magazine/social-media-marketing-for-cleaning-businesses/">2.7x more website traffic and 68% higher conversion rates</a> than those that do not post. One before-and-after photo can generate more inquiries than a month of door flyers.</p>
<p>The U.S. janitorial and cleaning services market generates <a href="https://www.ibisworld.com/industry-statistics/market-size/janitorial-services-united-states/">$112 billion in annual revenue</a>. Over 1.2 million cleaning businesses compete for clients. 90% of those businesses employ fewer than 10 people. Social media levels the playing field. A solo cleaner with consistent posts can out-market a 50-person company with zero online presence.</p>
<p>This guide covers which platforms to use, what to post, how often to post, and how to turn followers into paying clients. Every recommendation is built for cleaning business owners who clean all day and market at night.</p>
<p>We have published 3,500+ SEO articles across 70+ industries, including residential cleaning, commercial janitorial, and specialty cleaning services.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn:</p>
<ul>
<li>Which social media platforms work best for cleaning companies</li>
