<h3>Start With Facebook and Instagram</h3>
<p>Facebook reaches homeowners aged 30 to 65. Local community groups and neighborhood pages are where cleaning recommendations happen every week. A single "anyone know a good cleaner?" post generates 20 to 50 comments. If your business appears in those threads, you win leads for free.</p>
<p>Instagram works for visual proof. Before-and-after cleaning photos perform better than any other content type in the cleaning industry. The platform now prioritizes Reels (short video), which means a 15-second cleaning time-lapse reaches more people than a static photo.</p>
<p>For a deeper comparison of platforms, see our guide on <a href="/best/best-social-media-platforms-local-businesses/">best social media platforms for local businesses</a>.</p>
<h3>Do Not Ignore Nextdoor</h3>
<p>Nextdoor is the most underused platform for cleaning companies. Every user is verified by address. Recommendations carry real weight because neighbors trust neighbors. Claim your business page, respond to cleaning-related posts, and ask satisfied clients to recommend you there.</p>
