<h2>Short-Form Video: The Highest-ROI Content Type</h2>
<p><a href="https://sproutsocial.com/insights/social-media-statistics/">Short-form video delivers 41% ROI</a>, the highest of any content format. <a href="https://sproutsocial.com/insights/social-media-statistics/">85% of people say video convinced them to buy a product</a>. For cleaning companies, video content is the easiest win because the work itself is visual.</p>
<h3>What to Film</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Cleaning time-lapses.</strong> Set your phone on a counter. Hit record. Clean the area. Speed it up 4x. Post. 15 seconds. Done.</li>
<li><strong>Product demos.</strong> Show a cleaning product removing a stain. No script needed. The result speaks for itself.</li>
<li><strong>Satisfying details.</strong> Close-ups of grout cleaning, pressure washing, or window streaks disappearing. These clips go viral because they trigger a satisfaction response.</li>
<li><strong>"Most disgusting job" series.</strong> Show the worst messes you tackle (with client permission). These generate high engagement because people love dramatic transformations.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Tips for Filming</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Use natural light</strong> whenever possible. Open blinds before filming.</li>
<li><strong>Film vertically</strong> (9:16 ratio) for Reels and TikTok.</li>
<li><strong>Keep videos under 30 seconds.</strong> Shorter clips get more views and shares.</li>
<li><strong>Add text overlay.</strong> "Watch this kitchen go from gross to spotless" drives more views than no text.</li>
<li><strong>No need for professional equipment.</strong> Your phone is enough. A $15 phone tripod helps with stability.</li>
</ul>
<p>TikTok's engagement rate is <a href="https://sproutsocial.com/insights/social-media-statistics/">3.70%</a>, the highest of any platform. A cleaning video that gets 10,000 views generates 370 engagements. Some of those turn into leads.</p>
<h2>Running Ads on $5 to $10 Per Day</h2>
<p>Organic reach on Facebook pages has dropped below 5%. Paid ads amplify your best content to the exact audience you want.</p>
<h3>Facebook and Instagram Ad Setup for Cleaning Companies</h3>
<p><strong>Budget:</strong> $5 to $10 per day ($150 to $300 per month).</p>
<p><strong>Targeting:</strong>
- Location: Your service area (specific zip codes or a radius around your office)
- Age: 28 to 65
- Interests: Home improvement, interior design, cleaning, home organization
- Homeowners (Facebook allows homeowner targeting in many regions)</p>
<p><strong>Best ad format:</strong> Before-and-after carousel or a 15-second cleaning video.</p>
<p><strong>CTA:</strong> "Book Now" or "Get a Free Quote."</p>
<h3>What to Expect</h3>
<p>A cleaning company spending $10 per day on well-targeted Facebook ads typically generates 5 to 15 leads per week. At a 30% close rate and $150 average job value, that is $225 to $675 in weekly revenue from a $70 weekly ad spend.</p>
<p>Track results using Facebook's built-in reporting. Monitor cost per lead and cost per booking. If a lead costs more than $20, adjust your targeting or creative.</p>
<h3>Nextdoor Ads: The Hidden Opportunity</h3>
<p>Nextdoor offers local business advertising with hyper-targeted reach. Every user is address-verified, meaning your ad reaches confirmed homeowners in specific neighborhoods. Cleaning companies report lower cost-per-lead on Nextdoor than Facebook because the audience is pre-qualified by location and homeownership.</p>
<p>Claim your free Nextdoor business page. Post helpful cleaning tips in your local feed. Then test a small ad budget ($5 per day) targeting neighborhoods in your service area. The combination of organic Nextdoor presence and paid promotion performs well for service businesses.</p>
<p>For broader local marketing strategies, see our <a href="/blog/local-business-marketing-plan/">local business marketing plan guide</a> and our guide on <a href="/blog/market-small-business-no-team/">marketing a small business without a team</a>.</p>
