<p><strong>1. GBP posts boost local visibility.</strong> Cleaning companies posting weekly on Google Business Profile appear in <a href="https://www.zenmaid.com/magazine/social-media-marketing-for-cleaning-businesses/">32% more Map Pack results</a>. See our guide on <a href="/blog/gbp-posting-frequency/">GBP posting frequency</a> for the full data.</p>
<p><strong>2. Social proof drives reviews.</strong> Happy clients who see your social media posts are more likely to leave Google reviews when asked. Reviews account for 20% of local pack rankings. For review strategies, see our guide on <a href="/blog/get-more-google-reviews-local-business/">getting more Google reviews</a>.</p>
<p><strong>3. Brand searches signal authority.</strong> When people search your business name on Google after seeing your Instagram post, Google registers that brand search. Increased brand search volume correlates with higher local rankings.</p>
<p>For the full picture of how social media supports search visibility, see our post on <a href="/blog/does-social-media-help-seo/">does social media help SEO</a>.</p>
