<h2>Measuring Social Media ROI for Cleaning Companies</h2>
<p>The biggest frustration cleaning business owners have with social media: they cannot tell if it works. Here is how to track it.</p>
<h3>4 Ways to Attribute Bookings to Social Media</h3>
<p><strong>1. "How did you hear about us?"</strong> Ask every new client. Track answers in a spreadsheet. Simple and effective.</p>
<p><strong>2. Social-only promo codes.</strong> Create a discount code exclusive to your Instagram or Facebook followers. Track redemptions.</p>
<p><strong>3. UTM links.</strong> Add tracking parameters to the link in your bio. Google Analytics shows exactly how many visitors came from each platform and whether they booked.</p>
<p><strong>4. Direct messages and comments.</strong> Count inquiries that arrive through Facebook Messenger, Instagram DMs, and post comments. These are direct social media leads.</p>
