<p>If social media generates even 2 new bookings per month at $150 each, that is $300 in revenue. Against a time investment of 1 hour per week and $0 to $300 in ad spend, the ROI is positive for most cleaning companies.</p>
<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>Do cleaning companies need social media?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Cleaning businesses that post regularly see 2.7x more website traffic. Social media builds trust by showing your work. Before-and-after photos give potential clients visual proof of quality. Most clients research a cleaning company online before booking. An active social media presence with recent posts and reviews makes you the obvious choice over competitors with no online presence.</p>
<p><strong>What should a cleaning company post on social media?</strong></p>
<p>Before-and-after cleaning photos, quick cleaning tips, customer testimonials, team spotlights, seasonal checklists, and short cleaning videos. Before-and-after transformations are the single highest-performing content type. Take a photo before and after every job. Post them side by side with a short caption and your service area.</p>
<p><strong>How often should a cleaning company post on social media?</strong></p>
<p>3 to 5 times per week on your primary platform (Facebook or Instagram). Start with 3 per week to build consistency. Increase over time. Use a scheduling tool to batch-create and auto-publish posts. One hour per week is enough to create a full week of content.</p>
<p><strong>Is Facebook or Instagram better for a cleaning company?</strong></p>
<p>Both work. Facebook excels for community groups, local targeting, and reaching homeowners 30 to 65. Instagram excels for visual content (before-and-afters, Reels) and reaching homeowners 25 to 50. Start with Facebook if your clients are older homeowners. Start with Instagram if you create strong visual content. Ideally, use both.</p>
<p><strong>How do I get cleaning clients from social media?</strong></p>
<p>Post before-and-after photos consistently. Join local Facebook groups and Nextdoor. Run targeted ads at $5 to $10 per day in your service area. Respond to every comment and DM within 1 hour. Include a booking link in every bio and post. Ask satisfied clients to share your page with friends.</p>
<p><strong>How much should a cleaning company spend on social media ads?</strong></p>
<p>Start with $5 to $10 per day ($150 to $300 per month). Target homeowners in your service zip codes. Use before-and-after photos or short cleaning videos as your ad creative. Track cost per lead. If leads cost under $20 each, scale your budget. If they cost more, adjust targeting or creative before spending more.</p>
<p>Social media for cleaning companies works when you stay consistent and lead with visual proof. One before-and-after photo per day builds more trust than any sales pitch. The cleaning companies filling their schedules from social media are the ones that post regularly. Not perfectly. Regularly.</p>
